Merge raw data

Merge raw data

  • Paths and libraries setting
  • Generate R1 and R2 sample files
  • Generate a main sample file
  • Print generated sample file
  • Merge samples

Hans Schrieke and Julie Reveillaud

2021-05-30

Paths and libraries setting

# libraries
require(tidyverse)
require(kableExtra)

# paths
path_main <- "/Volumes/MY_PASSPORT/draft_final"
path_output <- paste0(path_main, "/output/0_useful_files")

Generate R1 and R2 sample files

# print script to generate samples files for R1 and R2
cat ../generate_R1_R2_files.sh
#!/bin/bash

PATH_MAIN="/Volumes/MY_PASSPORT/draft_final"
PATH_DATA=$PATH_MAIN/data
PATH_OUTPUT=$PATH_MAIN/output/0_useful_files

# export list of R1 and R2 sequences
cd $PATH_DATA
ls | grep "R1" > $PATH_OUTPUT/0_R1.txt
ls | grep "R2" > $PATH_OUTPUT/0_R2.txt
# run
bash ../generate_R1_R2_files.sh

Generate a main sample file

# create a sample file txt
Rscript ../create_sample_file.R
